<h3>Readability</h3>
<p>Sa11y can <strong>estimate</strong> the readability score from all paragraphs and list content. A good readability score is an indication that your writing is understandable and easy to digest. It is based on the average length of sentences and words on your page, using a formula known as the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flesch%E2%80%93Kincaid_readability_tests#Flesch_reading_ease">Flesch reading-ease test (Wikipedia).</a> A "good" reading score is between 60 and 100. Sometimes it may be difficult to achieve a good readability score. Most of your pages may say "difficult". Remember that this feature is only used to <strong>estimate</strong> the readability of your content. It should only be used as a <strong>reference,</strong> and not an indication of conformance. Sa11y calculates the readability score based on all paragraph (&lt;p&gt; tags) and list content (&lt;li&gt; tags). A low score does not affect the pass or fail state of Sa11y.</p>

<h4>Tips to improve score</a></h4>
<ul>
    <li>Keep sentences around 15 words on average.</li>
    <li>Avoid sentences greater than 25 words.</li>
    <li>Split long sentences up, or use bullet points.</li>
    <li>Avoid complex words or words with many syllables.</li>
</ul>

